(97, 174, NULL, '<div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"1\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid #3858f9; padding-left: 20px;\">\r\n                                                            <p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #1e293b;\"><strong>• NEW UI FOR COUNTRY PAGES CREATED </strong> — <b style=\"color: #3858f9;\">1h</b></p>\r\n                                                            <ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\">\r\n                                                                <li data-section-id=\"1bys2nn\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"145\">Working on the new Country Pages UI with a structured and responsive layout to display country-wise content in a clean and organized format.\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-section-id=\"12de4fi\" data-start=\"147\" data-end=\"302\" data-is-last-node=\"\">\r\nDeveloping dynamic sections for country details, listings, and navigation with an optimized user-friendly interface for both desktop and mobile devices.</li>\r\n                                                            </ol>\r\n                                                          </div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"border-top: 2px solid #f1f5f9; margin: 20px 0;\">', 'Ranjit Singh Shaktawat', '1.00', NULL, '2026-05-25 04:21:03', '2026-05-25 04:21:03'),
(98, 189, NULL, '<div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"6.5\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid #3858f9; padding-left: 20px;\">\r\n                                                            <p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #1e293b;\"><strong>• PROJECT MODULE CHANGES </strong> — <b style=\"color: #3858f9;\">6h 30m</b></p>\r\n                                                            <ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\">\r\n                                                                <li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n                                                            </ol>\r\n                                                          </div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"border-top: 2px solid #f1f5f9; margin: 20px 0;\"><li data-section-id=\"1yu0fo3\" data-start=\"15\" data-end=\"136\">Implemented dynamic project progress calculation in the Project Module based on Main Stages and Sub Stages percentage.\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-section-id=\"1fejmtg\" data-start=\"138\" data-end=\"266\">\r\nAdded logic to handle projects running in multiple stages simultaneously and calculated overall project progress accordingly.\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-section-id=\"muel6z\" data-start=\"268\" data-end=\"335\">\r\nIntegrated calculated progress into the Project Progress module.\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-section-id=\"hxa6rk\" data-start=\"337\" data-end=\"433\">\r\nAdded Pie Chart visualization in the Project Detail page for project progress representation.\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-section-id=\"1bqvgur\" data-start=\"435\" data-end=\"532\">\r\nAdded Project Progress Report section in Project Detail page with stage-wise progress details.\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-section-id=\"1r9njhn\" data-start=\"534\" data-end=\"631\" data-is-last-node=\"\">\r\nImproved project progress tracking and reporting flow for better monitoring and visualization.</li>', 'Manish patidar', '6.50', NULL, '2026-05-25 04:21:26', '2026-05-25 04:21:26'),
(99, 191, NULL, '<div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"2\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid #3858f9; padding-left: 20px;\" bis_skin_checked=\"1\">\r\n                                                            <p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #1e293b;\"><strong>• LEAD IMPORT FEATURE CODE ADD</strong> — <b style=\"color: #3858f9;\">2h</b></p>\r\n                                                            <ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\">\r\n                                                                <li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n                                                            </ol>\r\n                                                          </div><li data-section-id=\"12zymt1\" data-start=\"25\" data-end=\"95\">Successfully integrated Meta Leads Import functionality in WTS CRM.\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-section-id=\"28gqws\" data-start=\"97\" data-end=\"238\">\r\nAdded and configured required integration files, including:\r\n<ul data-start=\"163\" data-end=\"238\">\r\n<li data-section-id=\"3nozzb\" data-start=\"163\" data-end=\"176\">\r\nControllers\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-section-id=\"1if9u4s\" data-start=\"180\" data-end=\"201\">\r\nJob/Card code files\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-section-id=\"ir6mtn\" data-start=\"205\" data-end=\"238\">\r\nRelated integration setup files\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-section-id=\"1hvfo5q\" data-start=\"240\" data-end=\"319\">\r\nImplemented Meta lead import flow and connected it with CRM lead management.\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-section-id=\"1ai13uk\" data-start=\"321\" data-end=\"422\" data-is-last-node=\"\">\r\nTested the complete Meta Leads Import functionality and verified lead import process successfully.</li><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"border-top: 2px solid #f1f5f9; margin: 20px 0;\">', 'Manish patidar', '2.00', NULL, '2026-05-25 04:25:51', '2026-05-25 04:25:51'),
(100, 154, NULL, '<h1><b>Task Not Mantion Proper&nbsp;<br>Can Not Consider</b></h1>', 'Rahul Sharma', '0.00', NULL, '2026-05-25 04:26:45', '2026-05-25 04:26:45'),
(101, 154, NULL, '<div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"1\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid rgb(56, 88, 249); padding-left: 20px;\"><p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(30, 41, 59);\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">• ACTIVITY TIME </span>— <span style=\"font-weight: 600; color: rgb(56, 88, 249);\">1h</span></p></div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"margin: 20px 0px; border-width: 2px 0px 0px; border-color: rgb(241, 245, 249) rgb(145, 161, 182) rgb(145, 161, 182);\"><div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"0.6666666666666666\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid rgb(56, 88, 249); padding-left: 20px;\"><p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(30, 41, 59);\"><br></p></div><div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"2.5\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid rgb(56, 88, 249); padding-left: 20px;\"><p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(30, 41, 59);\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">• SYNCED THE MAIN_AIN DATABASE</span> — <span style=\"font-weight: 600; color: rgb(56, 88, 249);\">2h</span></p><ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\"><li data-section-id=\"7vfhi5\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"86\">Synced the <span data-start=\"13\" data-end=\"34\" style=\"font-weight: 600;\">main_ain database</span> and imported it successfully on the local system.</li><li data-section-id=\"1a7woyc\" data-start=\"87\" data-end=\"163\">Fixed the errors that occurred during the local database import process.</li><li data-section-id=\"cccrh\" data-start=\"164\" data-end=\"241\">Verified the imported database to ensure the required data was available.</li><li data-section-id=\"1csqfse\" data-start=\"242\" data-end=\"314\" data-is-last-node=\"\">Checked and confirmed that there was no missing data after the import.</li></ol></div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"margin: 20px 0px; border-width: 2px 0px 0px; border-color: rgb(241, 245, 249) rgb(145, 161, 182) rgb(145, 161, 182);\"><div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"1\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid rgb(56, 88, 249); padding-left: 20px;\"><p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(30, 41, 59);\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">• PROVIDED ACCESS TO THE BREAK TIME REPORT</span> — <span style=\"font-weight: 600; color: rgb(56, 88, 249);\">1h</span></p><ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\"><li data-section-id=\"psbnho\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"88\">Provided access to the <span data-start=\"25\" data-end=\"46\" style=\"font-weight: 600;\">Break Time Report</span> for Admin and selected Sub Admin users.</li><li data-section-id=\"9ynh7t\" data-start=\"89\" data-end=\"167\">Added role-based access control so only allowed users can view the report.</li><li data-section-id=\"ugjbwl\" data-start=\"168\" data-end=\"248\">Restricted the report from other Sub Admin users who should not have access.</li><li data-section-id=\"1irbjoz\" data-start=\"249\" data-end=\"345\" data-is-last-node=\"\">Updated the menu visibility so the Break Time Report option appears only for authorized users.</li></ol></div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"margin: 20px 0px; border-width: 2px 0px 0px; border-color: rgb(241, 245, 249) rgb(145, 161, 182) rgb(145, 161, 182);\"><div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"1.1666666666666667\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid rgb(56, 88, 249); padding-left: 20px;\"><p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(30, 41, 59);\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">• ONLY ADMIN SAN SHOW TOTAL REVENUE</span> — <span style=\"font-weight: 600; color: rgb(56, 88, 249);\">1h 10m</span></p><ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\"><li data-section-id=\"1e9ny15\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"74\">Restricted the <span data-start=\"17\" data-end=\"34\" style=\"font-weight: 600;\">Total Revenue</span> section to show only for Admin users.</li><li data-section-id=\"n4le85\" data-start=\"75\" data-end=\"159\">Added a role check so only users with <span data-start=\"115\" data-end=\"130\" style=\"font-weight: 600;\">role_id = 1</span> can view the revenue data.</li><li data-section-id=\"fynvmt\" data-start=\"160\" data-end=\"222\">Hid the <span data-start=\"170\" data-end=\"194\" style=\"font-weight: 600;\">order-summary-footer</span> from all non-admin users.</li><li data-section-id=\"1x6efmw\" data-start=\"223\" data-end=\"274\" data-is-last-node=\"\">Ensured other order list logic remains unchanged.</li></ol></div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"margin: 20px 0px; border-width: 2px 0px 0px; border-color: rgb(241, 245, 249) rgb(145, 161, 182) rgb(145, 161, 182);\"><div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"1.6666666666666665\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid rgb(56, 88, 249); padding-left: 20px;\"><p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(30, 41, 59);\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">• ADD POPUP ON BREAK</span> — <span style=\"font-weight: 600; color: rgb(56, 88, 249);\">1h 40m</span></p><ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\"><li data-section-id=\"lf05j0\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"66\">Added a full-screen break popup for Lunch Break and Tea Break.</li><li data-section-id=\"1y88mzn\" data-start=\"67\" data-end=\"146\">Blocked the screen while the employee is on break until the break is ended.</li><li data-section-id=\"1vcc3xe\" data-start=\"147\" data-end=\"211\">Added an “End Break” button inside the popup to resume work.</li><li data-section-id=\"1t29n35\" data-start=\"212\" data-end=\"311\" data-is-last-node=\"\">Implemented multi-tab synchronization so the break popup appears on all open tabs simultaneously.</li></ol></div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"margin: 20px 0px; border-width: 2px 0px 0px; border-color: rgb(241, 245, 249) rgb(145, 161, 182) rgb(145, 161, 182);\"><div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"1\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid rgb(56, 88, 249); padding-left: 20px;\"><p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(30, 41, 59);\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">• HOT WARM COLD IS NOT WORKING IN LEAD </span>— <span style=\"font-weight: 600; color: rgb(56, 88, 249);\">1h</span></p><ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\"><li data-section-id=\"151endi\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"54\">Fixed the lead sorting issue based on star status.</li><li data-section-id=\"1u725ks\" data-start=\"55\" data-end=\"116\">Updated the logic so <span data-start=\"78\" data-end=\"100\" style=\"font-weight: 600;\">3-star / Hot leads</span> appear first.</li><li data-section-id=\"z3v2nm\" data-start=\"117\" data-end=\"175\">Set <span data-start=\"123\" data-end=\"146\" style=\"font-weight: 600;\">2-star / Warm leads</span> to appear after Hot leads.</li><li data-section-id=\"1hobqx2\" data-start=\"176\" data-end=\"233\" data-is-last-node=\"\">Set <span data-start=\"182\" data-end=\"205\" style=\"font-weight: 600;\">1-star / Cold leads</span> to appear after Warm leads.</li></ol></div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"margin: 20px 0px; border-width: 2px 0px 0px; border-color: rgb(241, 245, 249) rgb(145, 161, 182) rgb(145, 161, 182);\"><div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"0.5\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid rgb(56, 88, 249); padding-left: 20px;\"><p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(30, 41, 59);\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600;\">• ADD LEAD COUNT </span>— <span style=\"font-weight: 600; color: rgb(56, 88, 249);\">30m</span></p><ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\"><li data-section-id=\"50i4r2\" data-start=\"29\" data-end=\"88\">Added <span data-start=\"37\" data-end=\"51\" style=\"font-weight: 600;\">Lead Count</span> near the user name in the Lead list.</li><li data-section-id=\"z98i52\" data-start=\"90\" data-end=\"167\">Replaced the previous <span data-start=\"114\" data-end=\"129\" style=\"font-weight: 600;\">Order Count</span> with total leads linked to that user.</li><li data-section-id=\"5ap28h\" data-start=\"169\" data-end=\"231\" data-is-last-node=\"\">Displayed the lead count using a badge for quick visibility.</li></ol></div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"margin: 20px 0px; border-width: 2px 0px 0px; border-color: rgb(241, 245, 249) rgb(145, 161, 182) rgb(145, 161, 182);\">', 'Rahul Sharma', '8.83', NULL, '2026-05-25 05:18:08', '2026-05-25 05:18:08');
INSERT INTO `task_follow_ups` (`id`, `daily_task_id`, `project_id`, `work_description`, `reference_name`, `time_taken`, `photo`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(102, 201, NULL, '<div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"0.5\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid #3858f9; padding-left: 20px;\" bis_skin_checked=\"1\">\r\n                                                            <p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #1e293b;\"><strong>• IMAGES UNDER PUBLIC WAS NOT WORKING</strong> — <b style=\"color: #3858f9;\">30m</b></p>\r\n                                                            <ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\">\r\n                                                                <li>&nbsp;Updated Laravel Blade image handling to use <code data-start=\"1055\" data-end=\"1070\">{{ asset() }}</code> instead of direct static paths for environment-safe asset loading.</li>\r\n                                                            </ol>\r\n                                                          </div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"border-top: 2px solid #f1f5f9; margin: 20px 0;\"><div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"0.5\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid #3858f9; padding-left: 20px;\" bis_skin_checked=\"1\">\r\n                                                            <p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #1e293b;\"><strong>• CORRECTED THE DATABASE WITH MISSING TABLES AND LATEST BLOG DATA, AND MAKE IT LIVE TO THE SERVER</strong> — <b style=\"color: #3858f9;\">30m</b></p>\r\n                                                            <ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\">\r\n                                                                <li>&nbsp;Prepared SQL queries to check missing tables/columns and create the required pivot table directly from phpMyAdmin.</li>\r\n                                                            </ol>\r\n                                                          </div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"border-top: 2px solid #f1f5f9; margin: 20px 0;\"><div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"2\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid #3858f9; padding-left: 20px;\" bis_skin_checked=\"1\">\r\n                                                            <p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #1e293b;\"><strong>• ERROR RESOLVED WHEN CHANGING THE API URL TO CRM.WARR, SERVICE PAGES WAS NOT WORKING</strong> — <b style=\"color: #3858f9;\">2h</b></p>\r\n                                                            <ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\">\r\n                                                                <li>&nbsp;Debugged Next.js Server Component error caused by using <code data-start=\"412\" data-end=\"421\">onClick</code> inside a server-rendered page and separated interactive logic into a client-side approach.</li><li>Added detailed API debugging logs in Next.js service page fetch function to trace response status, raw API output, and JSON parsing issues.</li><li>Identified Laravel production API failure caused by missing database pivot table <code data-start=\"738\" data-end=\"771\">warr_service_page_more_services</code>.</li>\r\n                                                            </ol>\r\n                                                          </div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"border-top: 2px solid #f1f5f9; margin: 20px 0;\"><div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"0.5\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid #3858f9; padding-left: 20px;\" bis_skin_checked=\"1\">\r\n                                                            <p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #1e293b;\"><strong>• UPDATED BLOG IMAGES IN PUBLIC FOLDER AND STORAGE FOLDER</strong> — <b style=\"color: #3858f9;\">30m</b></p>\r\n                                                            <ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\">\r\n                                                                <li>&nbsp;Configured <code data-start=\"156\" data-end=\"168\">.gitignore</code> to allow tracking of <code data-start=\"190\" data-end=\"210\">storage/app/public</code> while keeping Laravel cache/log folders ignored.</li><li>Resolved Git tracking issue for storage images using force add and cache clearing commands.</li>\r\n                                                            </ol>\r\n                                                          </div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"border-top: 2px solid #f1f5f9; margin: 20px 0;\"><div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"1\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid #3858f9; padding-left: 20px;\" bis_skin_checked=\"1\">\r\n                                                            <p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #1e293b;\"><strong>• SETUP AND FIX ISSUE </strong> — <b style=\"color: #3858f9;\">1h</b></p>\r\n                                                            <ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\">\r\n                                                                <li>&nbsp;Fixed Composer installation issue in this project by identifying corrupted <code data-start=\"80\" data-end=\"88\">vendor</code> setup and troubleshooting autoload generation errors.</li>\r\n                                                            </ol>\r\n                                                          </div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"border-top: 2px solid #f1f5f9; margin: 20px 0;\">', 'Jay Sahu', '4.50', NULL, '2026-05-25 09:30:53', '2026-05-25 09:30:53'),
(103, 201, NULL, '<div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"0.5\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid #3858f9; padding-left: 20px;\" bis_skin_checked=\"1\">\r\n                                                            <p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #1e293b;\"><strong>• CHANGED THE BLOG MODULE TO SHOW ONLY WARRGYIZMORSCH BLOGS</strong> — <b style=\"color: #3858f9;\">30m</b></p>\r\n                                                            <ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\">\r\n                                                                <li>&nbsp;Now only warrgyizmorsch blog will be visible and there is no option of selecting wts blogs, none from the filter.</li>\r\n                                                            </ol>\r\n                                                          </div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"border-top: 2px solid #f1f5f9; margin: 20px 0;\">', 'Jay Sahu', '0.50', NULL, '2026-05-25 09:33:14', '2026-05-25 09:33:14'),
(104, 192, NULL, '<div class=\"sub-task-item mb-4\" data-time=\"0.5\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid #3858f9; padding-left: 20px;\" bis_skin_checked=\"1\">\r\n                                                            <p class=\"mb-2\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #1e293b;\"><strong>• REMOVED MANY FRONTEND ROUTES</strong> — <b style=\"color: #3858f9;\">30m</b></p>\r\n                                                            <ol class=\"text-muted\" style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7;\">\r\n                                                                <li>&nbsp;Redirect the project to the /login page when \'/\' route hits.</li><li>Removed unnecessary frontend routes from web.php.</li>\r\n                                                            </ol>\r\n                                                          </div><hr class=\"sub-task-hr\" style=\"border-top: 2px solid #f1f5f9; margin: 20px 0;\">', 'Jay Sahu', '0.50', NULL, '2026-05-25 09:35:47', '2026-05-25 09:35:47'),
